ity Restroom              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       MRH/TBH 2-Person Apartment Common Area              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       MRH/TBH 4-Person Apartment Common Area              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       MRH/TBH Two-Person Apartment Layout              Go to the next slide    Go to the previous slide       MRH/TBH Four-Person Apartment Layout            Intern Housing   Intern Housing is available from May 24, 2020, until August 2, 2020. Minimum contract duration is one week.  Campus Housing has available accommodations for interns working in the Chicagoland area, whether you are local to Chicago or moving here for your summer internship.  Intern Housing accommodations feature fully furnished 2 or 4-person apartments with private bedrooms and shared bathroom, kitchen, and living room spaces.  Benefits of living in Campus Housing include:     No Hidden Costs: all amenities and utilities are included in our rates in addition to  free wireless internet  free laundry  free cable TV (must provide your own TV)  kitchen amenities available  mail service    24-hour Security  Location: Our housing is nestled in the heart of the city’s University Village neighborhood, which is home to many restaurants, coffee houses, and shops!  Community: Live among a diverse group of college students and other young adults with a similar mission who call University Village and UIC their home!   For more information, please contact our intern housing office at 312-355-6318 or housingintern@uic.edu .      Rates - Marie Robinson Hall & Thomas Beckham Hall     Marie Robinson Hall (MRH) and Thomas Beckham Hall (TBH) are apartment-style residence halls offering fully-furnished two and four-person units. All apartments are equipped with full kitchens, private bedrooms, and shared bathrooms.    Marie Robinson Hall & Thomas Beckham Hall Rates       Duration  Nightly Rate (per person)    7-21 nights  $48    22 nights or more  $45         Rates - Academic & Residential Complex     Traditional Double units have community bathrooms on the same floor, sharing with up to 18 other residents or guests on that floor. Semi-suite units have private bathrooms in their unit, shared only with other residents or guests occupying that unit.    Academic & Residential Complex (ARC)       Unit Type  Nightly Rate (per person)    Traditional Double  $35    Semi-Suite Double  $50    Semi-Suite Single  $55          Policies   Reservations To begin the reservation and payment process, apply online . Once you have applied, we will contact you with the next steps.  Terms & Conditions Please download, print, and sign our Intern Housing Agreement (PDF) .  Deposit Policy Any intern who wishes to reserve Intern Housing must submit a 10% deposit at the time of application. An application is not considered complete until deposit is paid. The remaining 90% is due 48 hours prior to Move-In. All deposits are non-refundable.  Early Move-In An early arrival starting on May 17, 2020, can be arranged for an additional fee ($100 plus additional nightly rates) – dependent upon availability.  Late Check-Out A late departure of August 9 can be arranged for an additional fee ($100 plus additional nightly rates) – dependent upon availability.  Cancellation Policy To cancel a reservation, email notice must be provided to UIC Intern Housing 48 prior to arrival. If notice of cancellation is received after an intern moves in, a charge of 50% of the remaining housing fee will be assessed.       Click here for Summer Intern Housing Application           Intern Housing   1250 South Halsted St.,  Chicago,  Illinois  60607    Phone: (312) 355-6318  Email: housingintern@uic.edu             GUESTS AND CONFERENCES    Back to main content           Guest Housing    Medical Students    Intern Housing    Conference Housing     Resources                    UIC Logo        Campus Housing         Future    Apply    Housing Rates    